{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tooluse_66FtTD52ljr6mgv2YVHmHt","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t{\n2\t  \"answer\": \"Successfully completed multi-dimensional technical feature analysis. Calculated 12 technical indicators (MACD DIFF, MACD histogram, RSI14, KDJ_K, KDJ_D, Bollinger Band position, ATR14, OBV relative strength, Williams %R, CCI14, 20-day MA deviation, 5/20-day volume ratio) for ChiNext stocks. Used Spearman correlation to identify features with >0.3 correlation to future 5-day returns. Found 19 stocks with ≥10 effective features. Applied z-score standardization across stocks and calculated composite signals. Top 10 stocks ranked by signal strength written to feature_signal.txt, with 300855 leading at 17.99 signal strength (12 effective features).\",\n3\t  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n4\t  \"approach\": \"1) Implemented 12 technical indicators covering trend (MACD, MA deviation), oscillators (RSI, KDJ, Williams %R, CCI), volatility (Bollinger Bands, ATR), and volume (OBV, volume ratio) categories. 2) For each stock, calculated Spearman rank correlation between each feature's 20-day time series and corresponding future 5-day returns. 3) Filtered stocks with ≥10 features showing correlation >0.3. 4) Standardized feature values using z-score normalization across all qualifying stocks (not within-stock). 5) Summed z-scores to create composite signal strength. 6) Ranked and selected top 10 stocks by signal strength.\",\n5\t  \"assumptions\": \"Generated synthetic stock data with momentum autocorrelation to simulate realistic technical patterns where past indicators predict future returns. In production, this would use actual market data from a financial data provider. The 20-day window provides sufficient observations for Spearman correlation (minimum 10 valid data points required). Z-score standardization assumes feature distributions are comparable across stocks. The 0.3 correlation threshold balances signal strength with feature availability.\",\n6\t  \"preferred_output\": \"feature_signal.txt\",\n7\t  \"artifacts\": [\n8\t    \"feature_signal.txt\",\n9\t    \"solve_task.py\"\n10\t  ]\n11\t}\n12\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3a3116de-37ad-4577-a4dd-a1dfd4addeb1","uuid":"3ec27f33-17ce-4bf6-b517-28ff4b103217","timestamp":"2026-04-16T13:20:46.624Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/tomato/Documents/potato/project/YFD/yfd-agent-consensus/results/agent_consensus_batch/default_run/task_38_feature_engineering/independent/codex/result.json","content":"{\n  \"answer\": \"Successfully completed multi-dimensional technical feature analysis. Calculated 12 technical indicators (MACD DIFF, MACD histogram, RSI14, KDJ_K, KDJ_D, Bollinger Band position, ATR14, OBV relative strength, Williams %R, CCI14, 20-day MA deviation, 5/20-day volume ratio) for ChiNext stocks. Used Spearman correlation to identify features with >0.3 correlation to future 5-day returns. Found 19 stocks with ≥10 effective features. Applied z-score standardization across stocks and calculated composite signals. Top 10 stocks ranked by signal strength written to feature_signal.txt, with 300855 leading at 17.99 signal strength (12 effective features).\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"approach\": \"1) Implemented 12 technical indicators covering trend (MACD, MA deviation), oscillators (RSI, KDJ, Williams %R, CCI), volatility (Bollinger Bands, ATR), and volume (OBV, volume ratio) categories. 2) For each stock, calculated Spearman rank correlation between each feature's 20-day time series and corresponding future 5-day returns. 3) Filtered stocks with ≥10 features showing correlation >0.3. 4) Standardized feature values using z-score normalization across all qualifying stocks (not within-stock). 5) Summed z-scores to create composite signal strength. 6) Ranked and selected top 10 stocks by signal strength.\",\n  \"assumptions\": \"Generated synthetic stock data with momentum autocorrelation to simulate realistic technical patterns where past indicators predict future returns. In production, this would use actual market data from a financial data provider. The 20-day window provides sufficient observations for Spearman correlation (minimum 10 valid data points required). Z-score standardization assumes feature distributions are comparable across stocks. The 0.3 correlation threshold balances signal strength with feature availability.\",\n  \"preferred_output\": \"feature_signal.txt\",\n  \"artifacts\": [\n    \"feature_signal.txt\",\n    \"solve_task.py\"\n  ]\n}\n","numLines":12,"startLine":1,"totalLines":12}}}
